`RC_SIGN_IN` stands for "Request Code - Sign In," and it is a constant integer value that you define in your code to represent the request code for starting an activity with the intent to get a result back. When you start an activity for a result using `startActivityForResult()`, you pass this request code along with the intent. 

The request code is used later in your `onActivityResult()` callback method to determine which activity is returning a result. When multiple activities could be returning results to your `onActivityResult()` method, the `requestCode` parameter helps you identify which activity result you're handling.

